# Beater Agent Context

Read `AGENTS.md` first. It is the compact startup map for this Rust workspace and
links to `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, and `CLAUDE.md`.

Key rules:

- One `beaterd` Rust binary first; service splits are thin bins over shared
  crates and need measured pressure.
- Standards at the edge: OTLP, W3C trace-context, OpenInference, and OTel GenAI
  are first-class. Native SDKs are accelerators, not the onboarding gate.
- Keep immutable raw envelopes plus normalized projections. Preserve tenant,
  project, environment, redaction, and audited-unmask boundaries.
- Do not hand-edit generated OpenAPI specs, SDKs, dashboard API types, or
  `sdks/semconv/conventions.json`. Use the regen workflow in `CLAUDE.md`.
- Vercel hosts the dashboard/stateless hosted surfaces only; `beaterd` and
  stateful workers run in OSS/local or hosted Rust cells.
- Keep PRs scoped. Do not edit `ARCHITECTURE.md` requirements or perform broad
  refactors unless the request explicitly calls for it.

Useful commands:

```bash
cargo fmt --all
cargo test -p beater-api
cargo test -p beater-api --test openapi_coverage
scripts/check-contract-sync.sh
cd web/dashboard && npm test && npm run build
```
